nodes.body: The proofs seem to be quite long. Is it possible to extract useful lemmas?

> The proofs seem to be quite long. Is it possible to extract useful lemmas?

The length is mainly due to writing an element in some span as a sum of fractions and clear denominators. I will think about if any of these can be extracted out.

> The proofs seem to be quite long. Is it possible to extract useful lemmas?

I golfed one lemma `ToSpec.carrier_eq_span` in #9601. Now #9601 is < 100 lines long which I think is an okay length. Could you please take a look at #9601?
